<span class="header1">EDUCATION</span>
<p>Occupations in this field involve educational institutions, such
as schools or colleges.</p>

<hr size="1" />

<span class="header2">Social Studies Teacher</span><br />
		<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A teacher shares information with
others.  As a social studies teacher, you would use your knowledge
of government, history, and geography to help students better
understand the issues that affect them in the world today. You would
make lesson plans, find materials, and present lectures.</blockquote>

	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>The traditional route to becoming a public
school teacher involves completing a bachelor's degree from a
teacher education program and then obtaining a license. However,
most states now offer alternative routes to licensure for those who
have a college degree in other fields. Private school teachers may
not have to be licensed but still need a bachelor's degree. A
bachelor's degree may not be needed by preschool teachers and
vocational education teachers; they need experience in their field
rather than a specific degree.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of social studies
teachers was $60,247 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />


<span class="header2">School Counselor</span><br />
		<span class="header3">Job Descriptions</span>
	<blockquote>School counselors assist students of all levels,
from elementary school to postsecondary education. They advocate for
students and work with other individuals and organizations to
promote the academic, career, personal, and social development of
children and youth. School counselors help students evaluate their
abilities, interests, talents, and personalities to develop
realistic academic and career goals.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Many states require school counselors to hold a
state school counseling certification and to have completed at least
some graduate course work; most require the completion of a master's
degree. Some states require school counselors to be licensed, which
generally requires continuing education credits.  </blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of school counselors was
$57,040 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Library Technician</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/GI/43282.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Library Technician" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a library technician, you would help a
librarian.  You would gather, organize, and maintain materials used
by library visitors. You would help visitors find information and
materials.  You would need good computer skills to do well in this
job.  You also need to enjoy helping people.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Most libraries prefer to hire technicians who
have earned a certificate or associate degree, but some smaller
libraries may hire individuals with only a high school diploma.
</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of library technicians
was $30,560 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

<span class="header1">SOCIAL SERVICE</span>
<p>The field of social service can be challenging.  It taps into a
person's resourcefulness. It also demands that he/she be very
involved with people.</p>

<hr size="1" />

<span class="header2">Public Health Social
Worker</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/EG/1212.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Public Health Social
Worker" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Social work is a profession for those with a
strong desire to help improve people's lives. Social workers assist
people by helping them cope with issues in their everyday lives,
deal with their relationships, and solve personal and family
problems. Some social workers help clients who face a disability or
a life-threatening disease or a social problem such as inadequate
housing, unemployment, or substance abuse. Social workers also
assist families that have serious domestic conflicts, sometimes
involving child or spousal abuse.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>A bachelor's degree is the minimum requirement
for entry into the occupation, but many positions require an
advanced degree. All states and the District of Columbia have some
licensure, certification, or registration requirement, but the
regulations vary.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of public health social
workers was $59,300 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

<span class="header2">Clergy (Pastor, Priest, Rabbi)
</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/EI/43007.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Chaplain" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Clergies lead religious worship and perform other
spiritual functions associated with beliefs and practices of
religious faith or denomination. They also provide spiritual and moral
guidance and assistance to members.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a master's degree in theology to become
a clergy. In addition, you would be "ordained" by a religious
denomination.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of clergies was $55,190 
in May 2019.</blockquote>


<hr size="1" />

<span class="header2">Human Resources Manager
</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/FG/43222.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Industrial Labor Relations
Specialist" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>In an effort to enhance morale and productivity,
limit job turnover, and help organizations increase performance and
improve business results, human resources managers help their firms
effectively use employee skills, provide training and development
opportunities to improve those skills, and increase employees'
satisfaction with their jobs and working conditions. </blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Many colleges and universities have programs
leading to a degree in personnel, human resources, or labor
relations. Some offer degree programs in human resources
administration or human resources management, training and
development, or compensation and benefits.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of human resources
managers was $116,720 in May 2019. </blockquote>

